For the given code below, Verilator will overwrite the value of @tt[0]@ with @c@ without giving any warning or error.
```
logic [1:0][31:0] tt ;
logic [31:0] a;
logic [31:0] b;
logic [31:0] c;

always_comb begin
  tt[0] = a;
  tt[1] = b;
  tt[2] = c;
end


```

FYI, VCS will report a out of bound warning and ignore the @tt[2]@ assignment.
